      "name": "Initial Claude Plan",
      "model": "claude-sonnet-4-6",
      "prompt": "I want to make a plan file. the objective in the end is to make a system that allows a drone to navigate using a only it's camera looking down. it will look directly down and compare to satilite footage. the drone will transmit it's footage to a computer that will proccess it and decide where the drone is. assume we have access to the drones height and compass and an approximate area that is accurate within a 100 meters area. so will be getting packets of height, the frame of what the drone is seeing looking down and the compass information (heading). I need you to design a vertical plan to impliment a neural net that does this. by vertical i mean that each phase of the plan will be something runnable that you can look at results at each step of the plan. for each step of the plan you will create 2 sections one for the AI Agent like yourself and one for the human. so the AI agent will write all the code and the human will do anything the agent can't like taking images and creating a dataset and actually running the training runs. you must also design a system to track what changes were made and create metrics to measure how we are doing. create a detail plan and put it in claude-plan.txt. you can use the research in the research folder if it helps.",
      "resume_session_enabled": false,
      "save_session_enabled": true,
      "save_session_name": "Claude Planner",
      "resume_named_session_name": "",
